[The most general science. Pythagoras is said to have called himself a lover of wisdom. But Philosophy has been both the seeking of wisdom and wisdom sought Originally rational explanation of anything, the general principle under which all facts could be explained, in this sense indistingnishable from science. Later the science of the first principle of being; the presupposition of the ultimate reality. Now Popularly, private wisdom or consolation, technically the science of sciences, the criticism and systematization or organization of all Knowledge drawn from empirical science, rational learning, common experience or wherever Philosophy includes metaphysics or ontology and epistemology, logic, ethics, aesthetics, etc'' - (The Dictionary of Philosophy edited by Dagbest D Runes, Jaico Publishing House Bombay)
